Summary: Provides methods for managing input properties like auto-advance, loop breaking, and reset behavior for animation transitions.

Method: is_input_loop_broken_at_end(input: int) → bool
This method checks if the loop for a specific input is set to break at the end.

Method: is_input_reset(input: int) → bool
This method checks if the reset property is enabled for a specific input.

Method: is_input_set_as_auto_advance(input: int) → bool
This method checks if auto-advance is enabled for a specific input.

Method: set_input_as_auto_advance(input: int, enable: bool) → void
This method enables or disables the auto-advance property for a specific input.

Method: set_input_break_loop_at_end(input: int, enable: bool) → void
This method enables or disables the breaking of the loop at the end for a specific input.

Method: set_input_reset(input: int, enable: bool) → void
This method enables or disables the reset property for a specific input.
