Document: AnimationNodeTransition
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodetransition.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the AnimationNodeTransition node, which controls transitions between animations.

Property: allow_transition_to_self
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, allows transition to the self state. When the reset option is enabled in input, the animation is restarted. If false, nothing happens on the transition to the self state.
Methods:
- set_allow_transition_to_self(value: bool)
- is_allow_transition_to_self() -> bool

Property: input_count
Type: int
Default: 0
Description: The number of enabled input ports for this animation node.
Methods:
- set_input_count(value: int)
- get_input_count() -> int

Property: xfade_curve
Type: Curve
Description: Determines how cross-fading between animations is eased. If empty, the transition will be linear. Should be a unit Curve.
Methods:
- set_xfade_curve(value: Curve)
- get_xfade_curve() -> Curve

Property: xfade_time
Type: float
Default: 0.0
Description: Cross-fading time (in seconds) between each animation connected to the inputs.
Note: AnimationNodeTransition transitions the current state immediately after the start of the fading. The precise remaining time can only be inferred from the main animation. When AnimationNodeOutput is considered as the most upstream, so the xfade_time is not scaled depending on the downstream delta. See also AnimationNodeOneShot.fadeout_time.
Methods:
- set_xfade_time(value: float)
- get_xfade_time() -> float
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimationNodeTransition
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodetransition.rst
Summary: This section describes methods for managing input properties in the AnimationNodeTransition class, including loop behavior, reset behavior, and auto-advance settings.

Method: is_input_loop_broken_at_end(input: int) → bool
Returns whether the animation breaks the loop at the end of the loop cycle for transition.

Method: is_input_reset(input: int) → bool
Returns whether the animation restarts when the animation transitions from the other animation.

Method: is_input_set_as_auto_advance(input: int) → bool
Returns true if auto-advance is enabled for the given input index.

Method: set_input_as_auto_advance(input: int, enable: bool) → void
Enables or disables auto-advance for the given input index. If enabled, state changes to the next input after playing the animation once. If enabled for the last input state, it loops to the first.

Method: set_input_break_loop_at_end(input: int, enable: bool) → void
If true, breaks the loop at the end of the loop cycle for transition, even if the animation is looping.

Method: set_input_reset(input: int, enable: bool) → void
If true, the destination animation is restarted when the animation transitions.